{"questionId":"23280","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A ball of mass 0.250 kg is released from rest at time <em>t</em> = 0, from a height <em>H</em> above a horizontal floor.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/a39fadb480d8759089a345b1497e892c1f3dca9f.png\"></p>\n<p>The graph shows the variation with time <em>t</em> of the velocity <em>v</em> of the ball. Air resistance is&nbsp;negligible. Take <em>g</em> = −9.80 m s<sup>−2</sup>. The ball reaches the floor after 1.0 s.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/64bfc03bb579497d416ebd747a788b97ad5fe258.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the average force exerted on the floor by the ball.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∆</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>250</mn><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><em>F</em><sub>net</sub> =&nbsp;«<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math>»&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>37</mn></math> «N»&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><em>N</em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>37</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>250</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>39</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math> «N»&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><br><em>Allow<strong> ECF</strong> for <strong>MP2</strong> and <strong>MP3</strong>.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"23280","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.1d.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the average force exerted on the floor by the ball.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","b